 p We are using the .NET API to IBM's WebSphere MQ.    

 p Creating the MQQueueManager object is clearly an expensive operation, and so we cache and reuse a pool of these objects.      

 p Currently, for each request, we access the required queues:     

 pre  code //obtain queueManager from pool 
IBM.WMQ.MQQueue requestQ= queueManager.AccessQueue(requestQName, mqOptions); 
